				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Aaaand, here are my quotes:</p>
<p>Stop:<br />
 I have made a display that measures all the time left in the world.</p>
<p>Ghost:<br />
“Where do you think you’ll go when you die?”</p>
<p>Gone:<br />
This is a story about a writer trying to tell a story about writing.</p>
<p>Outsider:<br />
“Stork Mating Habits” looked too well thumbed for its own good.</p>
<p>Cat:<br />
A perfect cat, it was: those shapely ankles, those precise whiskers.</p>
<p>Eye:<br />
Her clothes had been stolen from a hundred washing lines.</p>
<p>Subterfuge:<br />
It’s there if you know how to look for it: the jellied currents of the air, the slackness of fur, the stiffness of a smile.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

